quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,"When the sky is rent asunder"
  84,2,"and hearkens to the command of its Lord, doing what it should;",footnotes:182640:1
  84,3,"and when the earth is stretched out",footnotes:182641:1
  84,4,"and casts out what is within it and is emptied,",footnotes:182642:1
  84,5,"and hearkens to the command of its Lord, doing what it should.",footnotes:182643:1
  84,6,"O man, you are striving unto your Lord and you will meet Him.",footnotes:182644:1
  84,7,"Whoever is given the Record in his right hand"
  84,8,"shall be called to an easy accounting,",footnotes:182645:1
  84,9,"and shall return to his people joyfully.",footnotes:182646:1
  84,10,"But he who is given the Record behind his back,",footnotes:182647:1
  84,11,"shall cry for “perdition,”"
  84,12,"and will enter the Blazing Fire."
  84,13,"He used to live joyfully among his people,",footnotes:182648:1
  84,14,"thinking he would never revert (to Us)."
  84,15,"But no; (how would he not revert)? His Lord was ever watching him.",footnotes:182649:1
  84,16,"Nay; I swear by the twilight;"
  84,17,"and by the night and what it enfolds,"
  84,18,"and by the moon, when it reaches its fullness:"
  84,19,"you shall proceed onwards from stage to stage.",footnotes:182650:1
  84,20,"So, what is the matter with them that they do not believe,"
  84,21,"and when the Qur'an is recited to them, they do not prostrate themselves?",footnotes:182651:1
  84,22,"Instead, the unbelievers reject it, calling it a lie."
  84,23,"Allah knows best what they are accumulating (in their Record).",footnotes:182652:1
  84,24,"So give them the good news of a painful chastisement,"
  84,25,"except for those who believe and do good deeds. Theirs shall be an unending reward."
